        "created_at": "2021-12-17T10:31:54.665Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019m using FDB to do these things:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>set a key and increment it\u2019s counter</li>\n<li>if the key already exists in FDB, don\u2019t increment the counter</li>\n</ol>\n<p>When I use C bindings and run it concurrently, the transaction conflict occurs.</p>\n<p>My codes like:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">void put_key(std::string_view key, std::string_view value)\n{\n  auto tr = make_txn();\n  if (tr.get(key)) {\n    tr-&gt;add_counter_for_key(key); // using fdb_transaction_atomic_op and FDB_MUTATION_TYPE_ADD\n  }\n  tr-&gt;set(key, value);\n  tr-&gt;commit();\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Looks like other transactions may write the key when a transaction is reading the key, so there\u2019s conflict.</p>\n<p>Is there any problem for my codes, or my solution is not suitable?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 2,
        "updated_at": "2021-12-17T10:33:54.665Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
